This paper is focused on improving interpretability of reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper proposes a novel algorithm for creating decision tree policies via reinforcement learning, which is a technique used in the subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses tuning parameters to control the tradeoff between optimizing for smaller tree size or for overall reward, which is a topic relevant to the subfield of data science (cs.DS). However, the main focus of the paper is on improving the performance and interpretability of reinforcement learning, which is a topic that falls under the subcategories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.RO, cs.SY, and cs.DS.
